cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and text classification tasks.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper involves analyzing and extracting information from a large-scale review dataset.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes an end-to-end neural network architecture for detecting spoiler sentences.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper involves developing a computational approach for detecting critical plot twists in reviews.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with issues related to spoilers and their impact on media consumption and enjoyment.
